{
  "description": "## Small Crypt — Entrance to Thornfast Keep\n\nThis ancient burial crypt marks the entrance to Thornfast Keep. The stone stairs descend twenty feet into a network of dusty chambers that once held the remains of elven guardians who protected the Feywild crossing. The air is cold and still, carrying the faint scent of dry bone and ancient stone.\n\n**Zones:**\n- **Entrance Chamber (south):** A circular room with a descending staircase. Faded murals on the walls depict elven warriors standing against a twisting green fog. The stairs from the surface end here.\n- **Central Ossuary (center):** The main burial chamber, lined with empty sarcophagi. Their contents were plundered long ago, but the animated guardians remain. Two stone pillars provide cover.\n- **Western Alcove (west):** A smaller side chamber containing a bone chest and a collapsed passage that once led to the surface. Rubble litters the floor.\n- **Eastern Storage (east):** A former supply room, now home to a single ornate sarcophagus. The wardstone fragment — a key clue — is hidden behind a loose stone in the wall here.\n- **Northern Exit (north):** A reinforced door leads to stairs descending to the Garrison Halls (Medium Dungeon).\n\n**Atmosphere:** Faint motes of fey-touched dust drift in the torchlight. The undead here were once elven sentinels, their souls bound to guard the keep even in death. The Thorned One's corruption has seeped into their animating magic, making them hostile to all living intruders.",
